title: For Sale:  1984 VT700c Honda Shadow
postcontent:
WTT/WTS my 1984 1984 VT700c Honda Shadow
27849 miles.
Tires are almost new, still have the strip/nubs on the front, nubs on the back.
new plugs/wires.
Couple little chips in the paint, not very noticeable, touchup pen would do the job perfectly.
bike was laid down at about 15 mph...(underestimated the new tires on a dirty road...) bike is fine, just scuffed the highway bar/engine guard a little. windscreen has scuffs on the same side, but which were already on the bike when i got it. make your own assumptions.
seat is tearing, but is still very comfortable, especially compared to my sport touring bike. 
tachometer doesnt work, but according to the internet cowboys, you just have to pull it and resolder a couple connections.
looks damn good when cleaned up.

will consider trades for a smaller "womens" bike, older bikes are fine, but have to be in good shape, may need cash on top, depends on the bike.
street preferred, possible trade for dirt.
no yamaha xt 225s. i hate them. they are evil, rickety death traps.

comes with new stator and regulator, i will install them if wanted, or if youd rather pay a professional or do it yourself so be it. not  very challenging. the entire bike manual is online.
front forks are air charged, so if they ever need to be rebuilt(they currently dont) it's an easy DIY job
air/liquid cooled. engine has fins like most older bikes, but a fan and radiator as well.
auto-adjusting valves, noisy for a minute, but once you start riding(or let it sit, either way) they quiet down to a purr.
runs like champ, great bike for a young rider looking to move up to something bigger, or for an adult looking for a comfy daily rider.

i think i have a new oil filter for it somewhere...
comes with saddle bags in picture. 

1500obo

title: For Sale:  Springfield Armory M6 Scout .22 Hornet/.410 Survival Rifle
postcontent:
*I WILL NOT SHIP, PLEASE DON'T ASK.*

This is the very hard to find M6 Scout Rifle in .22 Hornet (not LR) over .410 shotgun. The parkerized finish is very good.

This one is very desirable in that it has no trigger guard which makes a HUGE difference when folding the gun in half. Most of them have a trigger guard installed which greatly impairs folding it and how compact you can make it. 
Another unique feature compared to other M6 is the .410 barrel has a much more open choke.  This means you can safely and effectively fire slugs, unlike in a full choked version.
The safety is crossbolt, unlike the newer type where the safety is part of the barrel selector.  This means you can just keep the hammer back on whichever barrel you prefer, and not have to awkwardly fumble with the safety and make sure you get the hammer set to the right barrel when the need arises.
Also has rear swivel stud installed. Holds 4 rounds of .410 and 12 rounds of .22 Hornet in the the buttstock. Not sure what the date of manufacture is but this was made in Geneseo, IL as opposed to Czech Republic like the later ones.

Comes with original cardboard box, no manual. 
Including 2 boxes of .22 Hornet:
10+ rounds Hornady V-Max 35 gr
20 rounds S&B soft point 45 gr

Asking $680 OBO. Will not ship. No trades.
Only selling because I acquired a different version of this gun and need to pay for it.  If you offer me $200 below asking price don't be surprised when you don't get a reply.  I know what these are worth and don't care what they cost 10-20 years ago.  Please don't just email me saying "call me”.  I communicate via email only, until I know a buyer is serious.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Springfield M1A Socom II EBR stock trade for LWRC R.E.P.R. 308 Scar 308 or POF 308
postcontent: Looking to trade my like new Springfield M1A Socom II for either a LWRC REPR .308, H&K MR 762 or a POF .308 Prefer the 20" barrel but 16" is ok. The M1A with EBR stock  is essentially a civilian version of the M14 EBR. Its a M1A socom 2 with a Sage EBR stock. Had the original EBR stock with adjustable butt stock but was way too heavy in comparison to the EBR stock with the M4 butt stock. This stock will accept any M4 / AR-15 stock and most any M4 / AR-15 grip. If not familiar with the Sage EBR stocks look em up and you'll find they are the best M1A chassis bar none. If you have any questions on the stock feel free to ask as I was trained on this weapon platform. The Socom II comes with 16" barrel, tritium inserted factory sights and very nice factory trigger. I installed the Sage EBR stock and outfitted it with a stripper clip mounted picatinny rail,  Magpul CTR buttstock and X products 50 round drum (new with box and papers). The pictures show a Surefire 951 weapon light, Urban ERT 2 point hybrid sling, Grip Pod fore grip and Aimpoint COMP M4 but I plan on keeping these. I have about 3200 in this set up without the light, grip, sling and Aimpoint. For the right trade I also have the original black synthetic stock, 10rd Springfield brand mag, about 8 Checkmate industries 20rd mags, 2 Checkmate Industries 25rd mags, replacement mag springs, some magpuls and 4 original Vietnam era GI 20rd Mags (various makers). This rifle has about 200 rounds through it and has been more or a safe queen than I would have liked. It did shoot sub MOA at 100 Meters with a Leupold  Mk4 LR/T 3.5-10x40  M5-FF using both Black Hills 175gr SMK HPBT and Lake City Match 175gr BTHP XM118LR. Shot right around MOA at 100 Meters using 175gr Privi Partizan Match HPBT no problem, yet never had a chance to test the 200-600 meter waters. I have a Super Match so this Socom II was mainly intended for tight spaces and under 100M usage, but it sat in safe most of its life.  I need an AR type 308 so looking to trade for a LWRC R.E.P.R. 308, HK MR 7.62 or a POF 308 preferring an 20" on the POF and either 20" or 16" on the LWRC R.E.P.R or a scar 308 but length of barrel is not a deal breaker ( I might come up with a real good excuse to purchase the 20" upper if traded for a 16" barrel, lol )   Email or  call / text me at 4O4-3I4-SeVen4O7 I can provide additional pics but it will only let me load one due to the size of the pic. Trade value of 3200.00 or Sale for 3000.00 cash FTF In OKC/MWC/Choctaw/Harrah area.
